===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|shoo|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|scōh||shoe}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*skōhaz||shoe", literally "covering}} (compare Scots {{term|shae|lang=sco}}, West Frisian {{term|skoech|lang=fy}}, Low German {{term|Schoh|lang=nds}}, Dutch {{term|schoen|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Schuh|lang=de}}, Danish and Swedish {{term|sko|lang=sv}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*skewk-}} (compare Tocharian B {{term|skak|skāk|lang=txb}} ‘balcony’), from {{m|ine-pro|*(s)kew-||to cover}}. More at {{l|en|sky}}.

